{
  "stem": "71.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they took us to another part of the camp, and we were sent out to the train.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were like in a animal-- you know, like the whole thing would open, the roofs.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Cattle.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Thank you.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We came to Germany, and we came to [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Camitz, ?] which is, you know, the southern part of Germany.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, well, some-- most of us slept, too, because we were laying on the floor.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And here, they ask us to come out, and we go into a train with plush red seats and backs.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I said to my sister, now I know how they-- how they take people to a crematorium-- you know, in-- in-- in luxury.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We went into that-- to the trains.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We all sat down.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Before the train start moving, we were all asleep.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we came into a little town, [INAUDIBLE], and they took us-- they took us to-- to a gate, black-- to a black gate.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I said to my sisters, well, now I know we are going to the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the gate opens, and a woman stays in the background, a big woman, and starts screaming at that [GERMAN] that was directing, you know, the transport, why do you-- did you keep these poor children for such a time without food?",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I have their dinner ready, and you are kept them-- you kept them for so long.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, when we walked-- walked into that diner, we could not believe out own eyes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were white, scrubbed tables, napkins and plates and forks and knives, and they served us cabbage with meat.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Of course, everybody got very sick after that because their stomachs were so empty, you know, that--",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
